TITLE: Creating Template Version with PHP cURL
DESCRIPTION: This PHP function uses cURL to create a new template version. It sets up the necessary parameters and sends a POST request to the Mailgun API endpoint with authentication and template details.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mailgun/documentation.git/blob/master/source/samples/templates/version-create.rst#2025-04-21_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
# Currently, the PHP SDK does not support the Templates endpoint.
# Consider using the following php curl function.
function create_template_version() {
  $params = array(
    'tag' => 'v0',
    'template' => '{{fname}} {{lname}}',
    'engine' => 'handlebars'
  );

  $ch = curl_init();

  curl_setopt($ch, CURLOPT_HTTPAUTH, CURLAUTH_BASIC);
  curl_setopt($ch, CURLOPT_USERPWD, 'api:PRIVATE_API_KEY');
  curl_setopt($ch, CURLOPT_RETURNTRANSFER, 1);

  curl_setopt($ch, CURLOPT_CUSTOMREQUEST, 'POST');
  curl_setopt($ch, CURLOPT_URL, 'https://api.mailgun.net/v3/YOUR_DOMAIN_NAME/templates/TEMPLATE_NAME/versions');
  curl_setopt($ch, CURLOPT_POSTFIELDS, $params);

  $result = curl_exec($ch);
  curl_close($ch);

  return $result;
}
```

