TITLE: Creating Mailgun Webhooks with Go
DESCRIPTION: This Go function uses the Mailgun Go SDK to create a webhook for the 'clicked' event. It registers a single URL endpoint to receive notifications when emails are clicked.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mailgun/documentation.git/blob/master/source/samples/add-webhook.rst#2025-04-21_snippet_6

LANGUAGE: go
CODE:
```
import (
    "context"
    "github.com/mailgun/mailgun-go/v3"
    "time"
)

func CreateWebhook(domain, apiKey string) error {
    mg := mailgun.NewMailgun(domain, apiKey)

    ctx, cancel := context.WithTimeout(context.Background(), time.Second*30)
    defer cancel()

    return mg.CreateWebhook(ctx, "clicked", []string{"https://your_domain.com/v1/clicked"})
}
```

