TITLE: Adding Email to Whitelist with PHP cURL
DESCRIPTION: PHP function using cURL to add an email address to the Mailgun whitelist. The SDK doesn't support this endpoint, so a custom cURL implementation is provided.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mailgun/documentation.git/blob/master/source/samples/add-whitelist.rst#2025-04-21_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
# Currently, the PHP SDK does not support Suppression Whiteslist endpoint.
# Consider using the following php curl function.
function add_domain_whitelist() {
  $ch = curl_init();

  curl_setopt($ch, CURLOPT_HTTPAUTH, CURLAUTH_BASIC);
  curl_setopt($ch, CURLOPT_USERPWD, 'api:PRIVATE_API_KEY');
  curl_setopt($ch, CURLOPT_RETURNTRANSFER, 1);

  curl_setopt($ch, CURLOPT_CUSTOMREQUEST, 'POST');
  curl_setopt($ch, CURLOPT_URL, 'https://api.mailgun.net/v3/YOUR_DOMAIN_NAME/whitelists');
  curl_setopt($ch, CURLOPT_POSTFIELDS, array(
      'address'=> 'bob@example.com')
  );

  $result = curl_exec($ch);
  curl_close($ch);

  return $result;
}
```

