TITLE: Using match_recipient Filter with Named Capture Groups
DESCRIPTION: Uses named capture groups in a regular expression to extract both the username and domain parts of an email address for use in a more readable forwarding URL pattern.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mailgun/documentation.git/blob/master/source/user_manual.rst#2025-04-21_snippet_24

LANGUAGE: python
CODE:
```
route filter : match_recipient("(?P<user>.*?)@(?P<domain>.*)")
route action : forward("http://mycallback.com/domains/\g<domain>/users/\g<user>")
```

